reviewText:
The music sounded as if it came from Charlie Brown
and the acting was off. They overacted many scenes
at inappropriate timing.  The writing was not believable.

This is a very funny, satisfying, thought-provoking short movie.  Yes, it manages to be both edgy and sweet.  It is reminiscent of Woody Allen films, but without any slapstick.  This is one of those rare finds that will make you seem oh-so-cool when you introduce it to your friends.
